TV presenter Richard Wilkins has retraced his grandfather George William Thomson's footsteps in Gallipoli as part of the New Zealand medical corps . 
  He made the pilgrimage on the eve of centenary ANZAC Day commemorations . 
  Wilkins read his grandfather's war diary at the NZ War Memorial in Auckland . 
  His grandfather was a qualified dentist who served in World War One . 
  He said the memories of his grandfather were 'deeply overwhelming'